post_text:
We are proud to announce Kinsey Arnold is one of 3 graduating seniors in the state awarded the SECU People Helping People $10,000 Scholarship. Selection is based on academic accomplishment, demonstrated leadership, excellence of character, integrity, and community involvement. Kinsey was nominated by the LSA Scholarship Committee based on required criteria and selected by the Office of Charter Schools.

Kinsey will be attending NC State University in the fall as an Exploratory Studies student where she was also selected for the Scholars Program. She plans to pursue a career in public health, where she hopes to have the opportunity to serve, heal, and advocate for the people in her community.

Longleaf Dance Middle School Masterclass Night: Ms. Mordecai will teach a master class from 6-7:15, and then students will enjoy pizza and have a Q&A session with current Longleaf dancers to learn more about the program from 7:15-8:00pm. post_text: Some of you may remember when Freebird McKinney spoke at Longleaf. Last night he represented the Teachers of our State at the National Championship Game! Way to go Freebird! We are grateful for your leadership and representation!
shared_text:
Freebird McKinney is attending 2020 National Championship Game with Dylan Huisken and 13 others at Mercedes-Benz Superdome.
January 14 at 10:16 AM · New Orleans, LA ·

We stood for our States, for our students, for our profession- GREAT TEACHERS CHANGE LIVES!

Thank you CCSSO - The Council of Chief State School Officers, Extra Yard for Teachers, the College Football Playoof Championship, the City of NOLA and all of the individuals and Education advocates who made this opportunity possible. The #NTOY19 Framily stood in unity and celebrated EACH and EVERY moment from this last year, our individual paths and our collective journey.

I love you all! I have loved representing as the NC TOY, and apart from being a husband, a father, and a #EducatorDiplomat, the true honor of my life. More to come as I reflect on this experience and the next steps of this blessed adventure, we call LIFE! Kelly Keen McKinney and I are coming home, to NC, to The Shire...

#CFBPlayoff #CFBFoundation #EdLeadNC

shared_text:
SCHOOLTRAVELORGANISER.COM
Study shows that access to theatre & drama can boost children’s academic performance

ARTS North Carolina
December 14, 2019 at 8:47 AM ·

Arts education is essential to students' success, not an extra. This is a civil rights issue about access. This is a human rights issue about our future.
text:
